modules.description: Generates 32-bit and 128-bit hash values from byte sequences using the MurmurHash algorithm. Accepts input as strings, byte arrays, and custom data structures serialized to bytes. Used for fast data integrity checks in networking protocols and in-memory data indexing.

Computes 32-bit, 64-bit, and 128-bit hash values from strings using the Murmur3 algorithm. Processes raw string input and returns numeric tuples representing hash outputs. Used for generating unique identifiers, data integrity checks, and consistent key generation in distributed systems.
